// db1 -> database name
// table name-> practice
Database Query:
    create database db1;
    show databases db1;
    drop database db1; 
    Backup for database: Backup database db1 to disk ='c://Chirag';
    Show all tables in databse: show tables;
    use db1;

Create table:
    create table practice (
    id int,
    First_Name varchar(50),
    Last_Name varchar(40),
    Mobile_Number varchar(10)
    );
Insert values:
    insert into table practice values(1,'Chirag','Goel',8708075681);
Insert values from table1 to table2:

update table:

update practice SET NAme='Chirag' where id=1;

delete record:
delete from practice where id=1;
    

Alter Command: Add, Drop Column, Rename Column, Modify , Add Constraints.
    alter table practice add column Father_Name varchar(10); // Add column
    alter table practice drop column Mobile_Number;          // Drop column
    alter table practice ADD Primary Key(id);                // Add Constraints 
    alter table practice modify id varchar(50);              // modify
    alter table practice rename column id to Roll_No;        // rename column
Show table structure:
    desc practice;
    
SQL (Structured Query Language)
It is non-procedural Language in which you specify what you want not how to get it.
Types: 1) DDL(Data Defination Language): provides command for defining relation schema, deleting relation, modifying relation
       2) DML(Data Manipulation Language): command to insert tuple, delete tuples and modify tuples
